      <Section>
        <h3>React Heading</h3>

        <p>
          <a href="https://www.schlopstop.com">React Heading</a> is my first published
          node package! I wrote this to solve a problem I was facing with conflicting
          HTML heading levels. With React Heading you can easily manage the headings
          in your app to be ADA compliant.
        </p>

        <div class={styles.coreTech}>
          <p>Core technologies:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>React</li>
            <li>TypeScript</li>
            <li>NPM Registry</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <p>Checkout the code on <a>GitHub</a> and <a>NPM</a></p>
      </Section>

